sources.postFetch:
unpackDir="$TMPDIR/unpack"
mkdir "$unpackDir"
cd "$unpackDir"

renamed="$TMPDIR/download.tar.gz"
mv "$downloadedFile" "$renamed"
unpackFile "$renamed"
chmod -R +w "$unpackDir"
if [ $(ls -A "$unpackDir" | wc -l) != 1 ]; then
  echo "error: zip file must contain a single file or directory."
  echo "hint: Pass stripRoot=false; to fetchzip to assume flat list of files."
  exit 1
fi
fn=$(cd "$unpackDir" && ls -A)
if [ -f "$unpackDir/$fn" ]; then
  mkdir $out
fi
mv "$unpackDir/$fn" "$out"


chmod 755 "$out"

sources.postFetch:
tmpfile="$TMPDIR/patch"

if [ ! -s "$out" ]; then
  echo "error: Fetched patch file '$out' is empty!" 1>&2
  exit 1
fi

set +e
cat < "$out" > "$tmpfile"
if [ $? -ne 0 ] || [ ! -s "$tmpfile" ]; then
    echo 'Failed to decode patch with command "'cat'"' >&2
    echo 'Fetched file was (limited to 128 bytes):' >&2
    od -A x -t x1z -v -N 128 "$out" >&2
    exit 1
fi
set -e
mv "$tmpfile" "$out"

lsdiff \
   \
  "$out" \
| sort -u | sed -e 's/[*?]/\\&/g' \
| xargs -I{} --delimiter='\n' \
  filterdiff \
  --include={} \
  --strip=0 \
   \
  --clean "$out" > "$tmpfile"

if [ ! -s "$tmpfile" ]; then
  echo "error: Normalized patch '$tmpfile' is empty (while the fetched file was not)!" 1>&2
  echo "Did you maybe fetch a HTML representation of a patch instead of a raw patch?" 1>&2
  echo "Fetched file was:" 1>&2
  cat "$out" 1>&2
  exit 1
fi

filterdiff \
  -p1 \
   \
   \
  "$tmpfile" > "$out"

if [ ! -s "$out" ]; then
  echo "error: Filtered patch '$out' is empty (while the original patch file was not)!" 1>&2
  echo "Check your includes and excludes." 1>&2
  echo "Normalized patch file was:" 1>&2
  cat "$tmpfile" 1>&2
  exit 1
fi
